To check kubelet status on a node :
1) ssh to node
2) Run :

        service kubelet status

3) If it in inactive state run :

        service kubelet start


Command to see node logs:

     journalctl -u kubelet

Note, kubelet configs are located in :

    /etc/kubernates/kubelet.config

kubelet files located at:

    /var/lib/kubelet/

After update in kubelet files run:

    service kubelet restart

port to connect node to control plane should be :

    6443


                        ****

to create a service from pod use the command :

kubectl expose pod <POD NAME> --port=6379 --name=<SERVICE NAME>

(By default the service will be created as "ClusterIp", will be accessible only inside the cluster)

    You can do the same for deployment:

kubectl expose deployment <POD NAME> --port=6379 --name=<SERVICE NAME> --type=NodePort

    (Node port type is accessible outside the cluster)